    "51 developed a faster inference algorithm for energybased models that computes a value to which the activity is likely to converge, termed latent equilibrium 51.",
    "Iteratively setting each neuron's output based on its latent equilibrium leads to much faster inference 51 and enables efficient computation of the prospective configuration.",
    "Predictive coding networks require symmetric forward and back ward weights between layers of neurons, so a question arises concern ing how such symmetry may develop in the brain.",
    "If predictive coding networks are initialized with symmetric weights (as in our simulations), the symmetry will persist because the changes in weight between neurons A and B are the same as those for feedback weight (between neurons B and A).",
    "Even if the weights are not initialized symmetrically, the symmetry may develop if synaptic decay is included in the model 52 because then the initial asymmetric values decay away, and weight values become more influenced by recent changes that are symmetric."
